PHASE 0  — Project Initialization — Django + React

This phase has no AI prompts — it is a set of terminal commands you run manually to bootstrap the project before writing any application code. Run every command in order.

0.1 — Bootstrap the Django Backend
Run these commands in your terminal from your project root folder:

💻  TERMINAL — Django Project Bootstrap
# 1. Create root project folder
mkdir school-portal && cd school-portal

# 2. Create and activate a Python virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate          # Linux/Mac
# venv\Scripts\activate          # Windows

# 3. Install core dependencies
pip install django djangorestframework djangorestframework-simplejwt
pip install psycopg2-binary django-cors-headers django-environ
pip install cloudinary django-cloudinary-storage
pip install weasyprint celery redis django-redis
pip install Pillow requests
pip freeze > backend/requirements.txt

# 4. Start Django project
mkdir backend && cd backend
django-admin startproject config .

# 5. Create all apps
python manage.py startapp tenants
python manage.py startapp accounts
python manage.py startapp academics
python manage.py startapp enrollment
python manage.py startapp timetable
python manage.py startapp attendance
python manage.py startapp gradebook
python manage.py startapp results
python manage.py startapp cbt
python manage.py startapp fees
python manage.py startapp notifications
python manage.py startapp analytics
python manage.py startapp promotion

# 6. Create settings split
mkdir config/settings
touch config/settings/__init__.py
mv config/settings.py config/settings/base.py
touch config/settings/development.py
touch config/settings/production.py

# 7. Create .env file
touch .env
cd ..

