I am building a multi-tenant Nigerian secondary school portal + CBT.
The project lives in: school-portal/backend/ (Django) and school-portal/frontend/ (React).

Tech stack:
  Backend:   Django 4.2 + DRF + PostgreSQL + Celery/Redis
  Frontend:  React 18 + plain CSS (NO Tailwind, NO Bootstrap)
  Auth:      JWT via djangorestframework-simplejwt
  Storage:   Cloudinary
  SMS:       Termii API
  Payments:  Paystack
  PDF:       WeasyPrint
  Deploy:    Docker → Railway (backend) + Vercel (frontend)

Multi-tenancy rules (NEVER break these):
  - Every school maps to a subdomain: slug.myplatform.com
  - TenantMiddleware resolves School from subdomain → request.tenant
  - EVERY model (except School itself) has school = FK(School)
  - EVERY queryset must be scoped: .filter(school=request.tenant)
  - TenantMixin on all ViewSets handles this automatically

Roles: superadmin | school_admin | teacher | student | parent
Nigerian academic: 3-term year, WAEC/NECO grades (A1–F9),
  CA (40%) + Exam (60%), cognitive + affective domain scoring,
  scratch card result system, admission numbers: SLUG-YYYY-XXXX

All apps are in backend/ — write to the correct app folder.
Always include: models.py, serializers.py, views.py, urls.py.
Always write clean, commented, production-ready Django/React code.

1.2 — Multi-Tenant Setup & School Onboarding
Personal note: The School model has a theme_config JSONField storing brand colors and logo. The React frontend reads this on load and injects CSS variables — one backend serves all schools with zero per-school frontend deployment.

🏗️  PROMPT 1.2 — School Model, TenantMiddleware & TenantMixin
Working in: backend/tenants/

Create the following:

1. models.py — School model with:
   name, slug(unique), subdomain(unique), logo(URLField),
   theme_config(JSONField: primary_color, secondary_color,
                            accent_color, font_family),
   address, phone, email, motto, registration_number,
   is_active(Bool), subscription_plan(free|basic|premium), created_at

2. middleware.py — TenantMiddleware class:
   - Parse subdomain from request.get_host()
   - Lookup School.objects.get(subdomain=sub, is_active=True)
   - Set request.tenant = school
   - Return 404 JSON if not found
   - Skip for paths: /superadmin/, /health/, /api/auth/

3. mixins.py — TenantMixin(for DRF ViewSets):
   - get_queryset() filters by self.request.tenant
   - perform_create() injects school=self.request.tenant

4. serializers.py — SchoolSerializer (all fields)
5. views.py — SchoolOnboardingView (SuperAdmin only, POST)
6. urls.py — /api/schools/ and /api/school/me/
7. admin.py — Register School

Then update config/settings/base.py:
  - Add 'tenants' to INSTALLED_APPS
  - Add TenantMiddleware to MIDDLEWARE (after SecurityMiddleware)
  - Add 'tenants.middleware.TenantMiddleware' path

Update config/urls.py to include tenants.urls

