6.4 — Railway Deployment: Django Backend
Railway is the recommended backend host. It supports Docker deploys natively, has a managed PostgreSQL add-on, and supports environment variables per service. Free tier is enough for a pilot school.

🚂  PROMPT 6.4 — Railway Backend Deployment Config & Production Settings
Generate all Railway deployment config and production Django settings.

1. backend/config/settings/production.py (extends base.py):
   - Read all secrets from environment using os.environ.get()
   - SECRET_KEY from env
   - DEBUG = False
   - ALLOWED_HOSTS: parse from ALLOWED_HOSTS env var
     Must include: *.up.railway.app AND *.yourplatform.com
   - DATABASES: parse DATABASE_URL using dj-database-url
   - CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGIN_REGEXES:
       r'^https://.*\.vercel\.app$'
       r'^https://.*\.yourplatform\.com$'
   - STATIC_ROOT = BASE_DIR / 'staticfiles'
   - STATICFILES_STORAGE = 'whitenoise.storage.CompressedManifestStaticFilesStorage'
