6.6 — CI/CD: GitHub Actions Pipeline
Personal note: The GitHub Actions workflow runs on every push to main. It tests the Django backend, builds the Docker image, pushes it to GitHub Container Registry (GHCR), and then triggers a Railway redeploy via webhook. The frontend redeploys automatically via Vercel's GitHub integration.

⚙️  PROMPT 6.6 — GitHub Actions CI/CD Pipeline
Generate .github/workflows/deploy.yml

Trigger: push to main branch

Jobs:

Job 1 — test (runs first):
  runs-on: ubuntu-latest
  services:
    postgres: image postgres:15, env POSTGRES_* vars, health check
  steps:
    1. Checkout code
    2. Set up Python 3.11
    3. pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
    4. Copy backend/.env.example → backend/.env (test values)
    5. Run: cd backend && python manage.py migrate
    6. Run: cd backend && python manage.py test --verbosity=2

Job 2 — build-and-push (needs: test):
  runs-on: ubuntu-latest
  steps:
    1. Checkout
    2. Log in to GitHub Container Registry (GHCR):
       registry: ghcr.io
       username: ${{ github.actor }}
       password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
    3. Build Docker image:
       docker build -t ghcr.io/${{ github.repository }}/backend:latest ./backend
    4. Push image to GHCR

Job 3 — deploy-railway (needs: build-and-push):
  steps:
    1. Trigger Railway redeploy via webhook:
       curl -X POST ${{ secrets.RAILWAY_DEPLOY_WEBHOOK_URL }}
    2. Wait 30s then hit /health/ endpoint to verify deploy succeeded

Also generate .github/workflows/pr-check.yml:
  Trigger: pull_request to main
  Run only: test job (no deploy)
  Add Django linting: flake8 backend/ --max-line-length=120

